[[File:NightsisterSithWitch-Mini.jpg|thumb|right|A Nightsister Sith witch]]
A '''Nightsister Sith [[Witch/Legends|witch]]''' was a [[Witches of Dathomir|Dathomiri]] [[Nightsisters/Legends|Nightsister]] who served the [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] and the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. Most learned to wield [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]] and could conjure [[Force lightning/Legends|Force lightning]], and their natural empathy with non-sentient animals made them powerful assets to their masters.<ref name="SWM:U">{{SWMiniCite|set=Universe|pack=Nightsister Sith Witch}}</ref>

==Outlaw Nightsister==
Sometime before [[13 ABY/Legends|13 ABY]], a single Nightsister [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Witch/Legends|witch]] had somehow managed to escape her imprisonment on [[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomir]] and formed a small [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]] band of Force-using outlaws. They greatly desired the ancient [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] secrets discovered by Luke Skywalker on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]], but knew that attacking while the [[New Jedi Order]] was at its strongest would have been suicide. However, when word reached them of [[Desann]]'s failed attempt at attacking the academy, they decided to attack while the Jedi's forces were still weakened.<ref name="Star Wars Miniatures: Attack on Endor">{{SWMiniCite|set=Attack on Endor Scenario Pack}}</ref>

They took advantage of the academy's chaotic state and struck quickly in their attempt to steal the Sith secrets from the base's computer. However, they had vastly underestimated the readiness of the academy and of [[Kyle Katarn]], who managed to repel their forces.<ref name="Star Wars Miniatures: Attack on Endor" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:SithWitch.jpg|thumb|Sith Witch concept art from ''[[The Art of Star Wars Episode I: The Phantom Menace]]''.]]
This character from [[Universe (Star Wars Miniatures)|''Star Wars Miniatures: Universe'']] was purely based on one of [[Iain McCaig]]'s early conceptual designs for [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]], which was in turn based on a nightmare McCaig had, since Lucas had described Maul as being "a figure from your worst nightmare". The look of [[Mother (title)/Legends|Mother]] [[Talzin/Legends|Talzin]], a Nightsister who appeared in [[The Clone Wars: Season Three|Season Three]] of the TV series ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'', was later developed from McCaig's Sith witch concept.<ref name="TCW">{{SWArchive|url=theclonewars/guide/episode312.html|text=''The Clone Wars'' Episode Guide: Nightsisters}}</ref>

